about.description: Acne is a common skin condition that occurs when hair follicles become clogged with oil and dead skin cells. This can lead to pimples, blackheads, whiteheads, and sometimes painful cysts.
about.commonality: It is highly common, affecting people of all ages but particularly prevalent among teenagers and young adults.

Avoid picking or squeezing pimples
